section.t:
If a route from ROUTE_AFI address family is received from a customer or peer, its AS_PATH MUST be verified as follows:


        If the closest AS in the AS_PATH is not the receiver's neighbor ASN then procedure halts with the outcome "invalid";


        If in one of AS_SEQ segments there is an customer-provider pair (AS(I-1), AS(i)) for which customer-provider verification procedure () with parameters (AS(I-1), AS(I), ROUTE_AFI) returns "invalid" then the procedure also halts with the outcome "invalid";


        If the AS_PATH has at least one AS_SET segment then procedure halts with the outcome "as_set";


        Otherwise, the procedure halts with an outcome of "valid".
